    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - Install - Brake Pedal</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Brake Pedal</title>
        <para>Prior to installing the brake pedal assembly, ensure that the brake pedal arm is seated and the dust cover
            is in place and not damaged.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0901065" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901065.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 87. Break Pedal Assembly Install</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BRAKE PEDAL ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. STEERING COLUMN MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. PIVOT BAR MOUNTING NUT AND LOCK WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BRAKE ROD RETAINER PIN AND CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BRAKE ROD DUST BOOT</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BRAKE ROD ATTACHMENT CLEVIS</callout1>
                <callout1>7. PIVOT BAR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert nylon bushings in ends of pivot bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert pivot bar and brake pedal assembly in position on steering column bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the pivot bar mounting holes with mounting holes on steering column bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert mounting bolt through bushings and pivot bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install lock nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901065">Figure 87, Item 3</hotlnk>), and hand tighten.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate align and install brake rod clevis to brake pedal arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901065">Figure 87, Item 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install retainer pin and clip (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901065">Figure 87, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten lock nut to torque value.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
